In [7]:
#         
#  CalinskiHarabasz  Silhouette    ,  DaviesBouldin - 

k_range = range(2, 6)  # 2, 3, 4, 5 
scores = {davies_bouldin_score: np.argmin, silhouette_score: np.argmax, calinski_harabasz_score: np.argmax}

handles=[]

for score, color in zip(scores.keys(), ['green', 'blue', 'darkviolet']):
    indices = []
    for k in k_range:
        labels = KMeans(n_clusters = k).fit_predict(X)
        indices.append(score(X, labels))
    plt.plot(k_range, indices, color=color)
    arg = scores[score](indices)
    plt.plot(k_range[arg], indices[arg], marker='o', c='r')
    handles.append(plt.Line2D([], [], color=color))
    indices.append(score.__name__)

plt.title('Clustering Scores')
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
methods = ["davies", "silh", "cali"]
plt.ylabel('Index')
plt.legend(handles, methods) 
plt.show()

scores = {davies_bouldin_score: np.argmin, silhouette_score: np.argmax, calinski_harabasz_score: np.argmax}

    indices = []
    for k in k_range:
        labels = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=k, linkage='ward').fit_predict(X)
        indices.append(score(X, labels))
    plt.plot(k_range, indices, color=color)
    arg = scores[score](indices)
    plt.plot(k_range[arg], indices[arg], marker='o', c='r')
    handles.append(plt.Line2D([], [], color=color))
    indices.append(score.__name__)

plt.title('Clustering Scores')
plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
methods = ["davies", "silh", "cali"]
plt.ylabel('Index')
plt.legend(handles, methods)
